# ⚡ PowerGrid AI — GridMind V2

A **multi-agent LangGraph** power grid controller for India.  
Uses **Gemini AI** + **live Tavily signals** to balance demand and supply across 10 real power plants.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
POST /chat or /run
        ↓
[location_agent]  → geocodes city, ranks 10 plants by distance
        ↓
[sensor_agent]    → fetches live weather / commodity / crisis signals
        ↓
[demand_agent]    → forecasts grid demand (base + weather adj + noise)
        ↓
[supply_agent]    → audits plant outputs, headroom, per-type totals
        ↓
[decision_agent]  → Gemini AI or rule-based fallback
        ↓
[apply_agent]     → enforces MW limits (skipped if all hold)
        ↓
[memory_agent]    → saves to SQLite
        ↓
[report_agent]    → returns structured JSON response
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
PowerGridAI/
├── api.py               ← FastAPI server — single entry point
├── requirements.txt
├── .env.example         ← copy to .env and add your keys
│
├── agent/
│   ├── flow.py          ← LangGraph StateGraph — 9 agents
│   └── grid_agent.py    ← Gemini caller + fallback logic
│
├── core/
│   ├── config.py        ← plants, cities, API keys, haversine math
│   └── memory.py        ← SQLite persistence
│
└── tools/
    ├── search_tool.py    ← Tavily web search wrapper
    ├── weather_tool.py   ← live weather signals
    ├── commodity_tool.py ← coal/gas/oil price signals
    ├── crisis_tool.py    ← crisis/outage detection
    └── distance_tool.py  ← 3-tier geocoder + haversine distance
```

---

## 🚀 Setup

```bash
# 1. Clone
git clone https://github.com/Sparsh2105/PowerGridAI.git
cd PowerGridAI

# 2. Virtual environment
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate        # Windows
source venv/bin/activate     # Mac/Linux

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Add API keys
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env and add your keys:
#   GEMINI_API_KEY  → https://aistudio.google.com/apikey  (free)
#   TAVILY_API_KEY  → https://tavily.com                  (free, 1000/month)

# 5. Run
uvicorn api:app --reload --port 8000
```

---

## 📡 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `GET`  | `/health` | Server alive check |
| `POST` | `/chat` | Natural language input |
| `POST` | `/run` | Structured city input |
| `GET`  | `/plants` | List all 10 power plants |
| `GET`  | `/memory/decisions` | Recent decisions from SQLite |
| `GET`  | `/memory/signals` | Recent signals from SQLite |

Swagger UI → `http://localhost:8000/docs`

---

## 💬 Usage Examples

### Natural language — `/chat`
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/chat \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"message\": \"heavy rain in Mumbai and coal prices are rising\"}"
```

### Structured — `/run`
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/run \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d "{\"city\": \"Bhopal\"}"
```

